article.headline: Troy 71, Middle Tennessee 57
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) -- Richard Chaney scored 15 points for Troy, which had five players with double-digit scoring, in its 71-57 win over Middle Tennessee State on Saturday. Cedric Jackson had a double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds for Troy (7-9, 2-3 Sun Belt). Boo Ramsey had 14 points and Justin Jonus and O'Darien Bassett each added 12. Middle Tennessee (6-9, 2-3) held the Trojans, a strong 3-point shooting team, to 1-for-9 from behind the arc in the first half while sinking seven 3-pointers. Middle Tennessee lead 33-27 at halftime, but a trey from Jonus gave Troy a 47-46 lead at the 11:52 mark. The Trojans never looked back, scoring a total of eight 3-pointers in the second half and holding the Blue Raiders to three. Jonus and Ramsey each had four treys. Kevin Kanaskie led Middle Tennessee with 17 points. Desmond Yates added 11 points, and Tim Blue had eight rebounds. Troy outrebounded the Blue Raiders 40-26, including 29 defensive rebounds.
